This paper deals with the evaluation of symbol error rate (SER) in digital communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a multiple importance sampling (MIS) technique called ALOE, which is a numerical method for efficient estimation of SER. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and simulation and modeling (cs.SI). The paper also involves statistical analysis and probability theory, which could place it under machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.MS).
